  <section id="basic-styles">
    <h2>Basic styles</h2>

    <h4>Page</h4>

    <p>HTML and body have the color <code class="language-sass">$color--text</code> variable applied to it by default</p>

    <h4>Links</h4>
    <p>Links are <a href="#">coloured the primary colour</a> and have <a href="#">no text decoration</a> by default.</p>

    <h4>Buttons</h4>
    <p>
      Buttons are now in here by default with some appropriate font sizing / spacing etc. By default there is o-btn with a hover/focus style and a disabled style.
    </p>

    <a href="#" class="o-btn">Check out this thing</a>

    <script type="text/plain" class="language-markup">
    <a href="#" class="o-btn">Check out this thing</a>
    </script>

    <button class="o-btn" disabled>Disabled Button</button>

    <script type="text/plain" class="language-markup">
    <button class="o-btn" disabled>Disabled Button</button>
    </script>

    <h4>Forms</h4>

    <p>
      Lots of default styling has been added for most input types and for selects, submits, buttons and checkboxes / radios. See snippets.md for the markup for a radio / checkbox. Elements are again 100% width as they'd usually be in a container. They are only defined as [type="text"] not input[type="text"] because they become hard to override with classes with the latter specificity.
    </p>

    <style>
