  <section id="recaptcha">
    <h2>Recaptcha</h2>

    <a target="_blank" href="https://developers.google.com/recaptcha/docs/invisible">
      developers.google.com/recaptcha/docs/invisible
    </a>

    <h5>Setup</h5>

    <p>
      Go to <a target="_blank" href="https://www.google.com/recaptcha/admin">google.com/recaptcha/admin</a> and create a new recaptcha key.
    </p>

    <p>
      As well as the live domain, make sure to include the following domains when setting up.

      <ul>
        <li>localhost</li>
        <li>docker.test</li>
        <li>REPLACE_ME_WITH_PROJECT_NAME.wilddogdevelopment.com</li>
      </ul>
    </p>

    <p>
      Once done, ensure that the google recaptcha script is included at the bottom of the <code class="language-markup">&lt;head></code> element in <code>src/templates/includes/_head.njk</code> and set the value of <code class="language-js">window.recaptchaKey</code> with the 'Site Key' from the recaptcha you just created.
    </p>

    <pre class="language-markup"><code><!--
    <head>
      ...

      <script src='https://www.google.com/recaptcha/api.js' async defer/></script>

      <script>
        window.recaptchaKey = '6LcqPbgUAAAAADzSyygzDiduNftUvKuw5NMCla_a'
      </script>
    </head>
    --></code></pre>

    <p>
      Now make sure that our recaptcha.js module is included in <code>src/js/main.js</code> and initialised.
    </p>

    <pre>
      <code class="language-js">
        ...
        
        import { setupRecaptcha } from './modules/recaptcha';
        

        function initialise() {
          ... 
          
          setupRecaptcha();
        }
      </code>
    </pre>

    <p>We are now ready to use recaptcha on our forms.</p>


